d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 2909 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Ahmad Shakir Zuhrah said, \u201cIt is a just pact such as the Hilf\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9935,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/24\/just-alliances-confirmed-islam\/","url_meta":{"origin":4345,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Alliances: Just pacts before Islam are affirmed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Amr ibn Shuaib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever is party to a just pact during the time of ignorance, then Islam does not increase it but in strength.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad 570 Grade: Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0634\u064f\u0639\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0628\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21056,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/10\/19\/best-islam-safe\/","url_meta":{"origin":4345,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Islam: Best practice of Islam is to make people safe","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 19, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: A man asked, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, whose\u00a0Islam is best?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThose from whose tongue and hand people are safe.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 6753 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14031,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/06\/ibn-al-qayyim-sharia-justice\/","url_meta":{"origin":4345,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Qayyim on Sharia: Justice is the objective of law in Islam","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim said, \u201cAllah Almighty has made clear by many of His laws that the purpose is to establish justice between His servants and for people to behave fairly. Whichever path leads to justice and fairness is part of the religion and does not contradict it.\u201d Source: al-\u1e6curuq al-H\u0323ikm\u012bya 1\/13\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14152,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/12\/dawah-muhammad-killing-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":4345,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Da&#8217;wah: People will say Muhammad kills his companions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 12, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdu